<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-28T16:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-28T16:36:00-05:00" n="739" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d739">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/11756.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-28T15:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 28, 1914, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I beg to quote the following communication just received from British
                            Admiral Cradock: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>If you will permit me, in consequence of difficulty you may
                                    perhaps have in communicating with Brazilian Minister in Mexico,
                                    I propose pending contrary instructions to contrive to do all in
                                    my power as heretofore in the interests of the United States of
                                    America, observing at the same time strict neutrality. Should
                                    you desire to do so, will you most kindly inform Washington.</p>
                                <p rend="right">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Christopher Cradock</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Rear Admiral, British Navy</hi>.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>